250 g Ground Beef
200 g Chow Mein Noodles
2 unit(s) Green Onion
9 g Sesame Seeds
1 tbsp Garlic Puree
4 tbsp Soy Sauce
4 tbsp Hoisin Sauce
113 g Sugar Snap Peas
1 tsp Sugar*
½ tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Add noodles to the boiling water.
Cook uncovered until tender, 1-2 min.
Drain noodles, reserving 1/4 cup (1/2 cup) noodle water, then rinse under warm water. Return noodles to the same pot, off heat.

Thinly slice green onions.
Halve sugar snap peas crosswise.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat. When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then beef, garlic puree, sesame seeds, half the green onions and 1 tsp (2 tsp) sugar. Cook, breaking up beef into smaller pieces, until no pink remains, 4-5 min.**
Transfer beef to a medium bowl. Set aside.

Reheat the same pan over medium heat.
When hot, add sugar snap peas. Cook stirring often until tender crisp, 4-5 min.

Add beef, sugar snap peas, soy sauce, hoisin sauce and reserved noodle water to the large pot with the noodles. Stir to combine.
Divide scallion beef noodles between bowls.
Sprinkle remaining green onions over top.

If you've opted to get beef, cook it in the same way the recipe instructs you to cook the turkey.**